**Police Scanner Stream and Chat Microservice**


Introduction

Welcome to the Police Scanner Stream and Chat Microservice. This innovative tool enables users to tune into live police scanner feeds and
 participate in community discussions through an integrated chat feature. Utilizing AssemblyAI's cutting-edge API, the service offers real-time transcription 
 of the audio stream, making it accessible and convenient.

Getting Started

Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following:

Node.js installed on your machine
An active API key from AssemblyAI
Installation
Follow these steps to get your microservice up and running:

Clone the repository to your local machine.
Run npm install in the cloned directory to install all necessary dependencies.
Insert your AssemblyAI API key in the server's configuration file.
Launch the server with the command node server.js.
How to Use the Microservice
Programmatically Requesting Data
To initiate the audio stream and receive transcriptions, you need to make a GET request to the /start-audio-stream endpoint.

Example Request:
javascript
Copy code
fetch('http://localhost:3000/start-audio-stream')
  .then(response => response.text())
  .then(data => console.log(data))
  .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
Programmatically Receiving Data
The microservice sends data to clients in real-time using WebSockets. Follow these steps to connect to the WebSocket server and receive transcription updates.

Example WebSocket Connection:
javascript
Copy code
const socket = io.connect('http://localhost:3000');

socket.on('transcription update', function(data) {
  console.log('Transcription:', data);
});
